---
import UseCase from '../../../UseCase.astro';
import UseCaseInteractive from '../../../UseCaseInteractive.astro';
import Usage from '../../../Usage.astro';
import UsageItem from '../../../UsageItem.astro';
---

<UseCase
  title="Set Expectations Over Time, Not Just Once"
  description="Reinforce what the AI can do and what the user's role is at key moments—not only on first use. Remind when context changes or when the stakes are high."
>
  <UseCaseInteractive clsHeight={112} label="Expectations over time" toggle>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full">
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Reinforce at Key Moments</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >Before sending: This will go to 12 people. Review the suggested text—you're responsible
            for what you send. [Edit] [Send]</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >Just-in-time reminder of scope and user responsibility when the action is
            consequential.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>When Stakes or Context Change</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >You're about to use this in a legal document. Our suggestions are drafts only; have a
            qualified professional review before relying on them. [Continue] [Learn more]</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >When the user enters a high-stakes context, expectations are restated.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-status-error-10 border border-status-error-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-200">
            <mds-icon name="mi/outline/error" class="text-status-error-05"></mds-icon>
            <mds-text typography="label"><b>Only on First Use (Problematic)</b></mds-text>
          </div>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >One-time onboarding: "The AI suggests; you decide." Then no reminder when sending to
            hundreds of people or when the user switches to a high-risk domain. Users forget or
            never read the fine print.</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-status-error-06"
            >Expectations fade; users slip into overtrust or forget their role when it matters most.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </UseCaseInteractive>
  <Usage>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Repeat or reinforce scope, reliability, and user role at important moments (e.g. before send,
      before high-stakes use).
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Rely only on first-use or one-time messaging; assume users will remember.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      When the context becomes higher-stakes (e.g. legal, external audience), restate limitations
      and user responsibility.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Treat every interaction the same; avoid reminding when the cost of misunderstanding is high.
    </UsageItem>
  </Usage>
</UseCase>
